    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/cointracker/b4f90d54-1df0-453e-af0d-875ffb7257f0/application",
    "company": "CoinTracker",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "44e1a4cf81e56bf2",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "OVERVIEW\n\nCoinTracker https://www.cointracker.io/ makes cryptocurrency portfolio tracking and tax compliance simple. CoinTracker enables consumers and businesses to seamlessly track their cryptocurrency portfolio, investment performance, taxes, and more. We are a globally distributed team on a mission to enable everyone in the world to use crypto with peace of mind. Learn more https://www.notion.so/cointracker/CoinTracker-is-Hiring-7308c712493940a3b6e62257d283dad8 about our mission, culture, and hiring process.\n\n\n\nSOME THINGS WE’RE PROUD OF\n\n - 🛠️ Building foundational tools in the cryptocurrency space\n\n - 📄 Over 1M tax forms generated\n\n - 💲 $250B+ in cryptocurrency is tracked on CoinTracker (~over 5% of the entire crypto market)\n\n - 🤝 Partnered with Coinbase, H\u0026R Block, Intuit TurboTax, MetaMask, OpenSea, Phantom, Solana, and Uniswap\n\n - 🗺️ Founders: Jon https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonlerner/ previously built TextNow (200M downloads), Chandan https://www.linkedin.com/in/clodha/ was previously a product manager at Google \u0026 Google[x]\n\n - 💼 $100M+ venture capital raised from Accel, General Catalyst, Y Combinator, Initialized Capital, Coinbase Ventures, Kraken Ventures, Intuit Ventures, 776 Ventures, Balaji Srinivasan https://twitter.com/balajis, Claire Hughes Johnson https://twitter.com/chughesjohnson, Gokul Rajaram https://twitter.com/gokulr, Serena Williams https://twitter.com/serenawilliams, Zach Perret https://twitter.com/zachperret\n\n - 🌴 Awesome benefits https://www.notion.so/cointracker/Benefits-b5db95c6d3224ab1ae3a384048cbaee3\n\n\nYOUR MISSION\n\nCoinTracker serves over 3 million users, partners with industry leaders including Coinbase and Intuit, and tracks $50B+ in crypto. As we continue our expansion from a single product into a multi-product platform, our infrastructure needs to evolve just as fast.\n\nThe Engineering Manager for Infrastructure and Platform will build and evolve CoinTracker’s infrastructure and platform foundations so our teams can ship products faster, scale reliably to millions of users, and leverage AI across the development lifecycle to unlock step-function gains in engineering productivity.\n\n\nYOUR ONE YEAR OUTCOMES\n\n - Architect and deliver the infrastructure foundations needed to support CoinTracker’s expansion to 3+ products and 3M+ users, ensuring the platform scales reliably without infrastructure costs growing linearly\n\n - Meaningfully increase engineering velocity by shipping platform capabilities (e.g., ephemeral environments, streamlined CI/CD, and self-service tooling) that reduce friction and increase deployment confidence\n\n - Evolve our development stack to be AI-native, enabling step-function productivity improvements through AI coding agents, automated testing and review, intelligent debugging, and AI-assisted operational tooling\n\n - Establish shared platform services such as authentication, audit logging, and observability, as the default across product teams, replacing fragmented implementations with a unified and trusted platform layer\n\n - Define and communicate a clear technical vision for Infrastructure and Platform that aligns teams around where CoinTracker's architecture needs to be in 2-3 years, not just where it is today\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Lead and grow a team of 5+ engineers across Infrastructure, DevOps and SRE, setting clear priorities, coaching engineers to their full potential, and hiring the next wave of talent as the teams scale\n\n - Own the roadmap for infrastructure reliability, developer experience, and AI enablement in development lifecycle. Make deliberate bets on what to build, buy, or retire as CoinTracker becomes a multi-product, AI-native company\n\n - Drive the evolution of CoinTracker's architecture toward modular, service-oriented systems, creating the shared platform layer on which we build each product\n\n - Champion a culture of platform thinking and technical rigor: proactively owning cross-cutting concerns, production readiness by default, and responsible AI adoption to serve millions of users handling complex financial data\n\n\nWHAT WE LOOK FOR\n\n - Role-agnostic\n   \n   - Impact: Demonstrated ability to drive business impact\n   \n   - Mission alignment: Hungry and motivated about making progress towards our mission of Enabling everyone in the world to use crypto with peace of mind.\n   \n   - Trust: Say what you believe. Do what you say.\n   \n   - Communication: Able to clearly talk about the details and also zoom out to the bigger picture\n\n - Role-specific\n   \n   - 2+ years of engineering management experience leading infrastructure and software platform teams\n   \n   - 6+ years of hands-on experience in infrastructure and software platform engineering\n   \n   - Deep expertise in cloud infrastructure (GCP preferred, or AWS/Azure), observability, CI/CD, and modern infrastructure-as-code practices\n   \n   - Experience building or scaling shared platform services (e.g., authentication, internal APIs, service frameworks)\n   \n   - Comfortable navigating ambiguity and turning loosely defined problems into clear action plans with pragmatic trade-offs\n   \n   - Strong architectural instincts and ability to guide teams toward sustainable, scalable solutions\n   \n   - [Bonus] Experience in crypto or financial systems where uptime directly affects users' financial well-being\n\nThe starting salary for this position is between $264,000 - $297,000 USD. Candidate's location does not impact the posted salary range. The actual compensation offered will be based on a variety of job-related factors including relevant skills, education, and experience. This position also includes equity in CoinTracker and benefits like medical, dental, vision, 401(k), life insurance, and PTO.",
